git init → To initialoze the new git repository.

git clone <repo_url> → To copy the existing git repository on local machine.

git status → To check the current repository changes like changes, staged files.

git add <file> → To add the file in staging area.

git add . → To add all the files in staging area.

git commit -m "message" → To commit all staging files with message.

git commit -a -m "message" → To Commit all the track files with message.

git branch → To check the branches.

git branch <branch_name> → To create the new branch.

git checkout <branch_name> → To switch the branch.

git checkout -b <branch_name> → To create the new branch and switch at the same time.

git merge <branch_name> → To merge the branch with current branch.

git remote add <repo_name> <repo_url> -> To connect the remote repository with local repository

git remote -v → To check the list of remote repositories.

git push <repo_name> <branch_name> → To push the changes in repository branch.

git pull <repo_name> <branch_name> → It fetch the changes from remote repository and merge the branch

git fetch <repo_name> <branch_name> → It fetch the changes from remote repository.

git log → To check the commit history.

git log --oneline → To check the commit Short log.

git diff → To check the changes of uncommit file.

git show <commit_id> → To check the details of specific commit.

git checkout -- <file> → To discard the changes in file and back to last commit.

git reset <file> → To unstaged the file.

git revert <commit_id> → To undo the commit.

git reset --hard <commit_id> → It delete the commit history and content of the file.

git tag <tag_name> <commit_id> → To tag the specific commit.

git push <repo_name> <branch_name> --tags -> To push the repository with all tags

git push <repo_name> <branch_name> <tag_name> → To push the repository with specific tag.
